# Conventional Commit Template

# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, chore, ci
# Scope: optional module or area (e.g., navbar, auth)
# Subject: imperative, lower-case, no trailing period
#
# Body: motivation and context. Wrap at 72 chars.
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: describe breaking change and migration path

# Examples
# feat(navbar): add active link styling
# fix(button): correct ghost variant colors
# docs(readme): add local dev instructions

